.TH IW 8 "7 June 2012" "iw" "Linux"
.SH NAME
iw \- show / manipulate wireless devices n' they configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS

.ad l
.in +8
.ti -8
.B iw
.RI [ " OPTIONS " ] " " { "
.BR help " [ "
.RI ""command " ]"
.BR "|"
.RI ""OBJECT " " COMMAND " }"
.sp

.ti -8
.IR OBJECT " := { "
.BR dev " | " phy " | " reg " }"
.sp

.ti -8
.IR OPTIONS " := { --version | --debug }"

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.BR " --version"
print version shiznit n' exit.

.TP
.BR " --debug"
enable netlink message debugging.

.SH IW - COMMAND SYNTAX

.SS
.I OBJECT

.TP
.B dev <interface name>
- network intercourse.

.TP
.B phy <phy name>
- wireless hardware thang (by name).
.TP
.B phy#<phy index>
- wireless hardware thang (by index).

.TP
.B reg
- regulatory agent.

.SS
.I COMMAND

Specifies tha action ta big-ass up on tha object.
Da set of possible actions dependz on tha object type.
.B iw help
will print all supported commands, while
.B iw help command
will print tha help fo' all matchin commands.

